<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - LOW AND
        HIGH PRESSURE SWITCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>LOW AND HIGH PRESSURE SWITCH</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch is off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the covers from the passenger side of the instrument panel and the Blend-air
                    unit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the low and/or high pressure switch from the wiring harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using two wrenches, remove the low and/or high pressure switch from the adapter on the
                    evaporator outlet pipe (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601421">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601421" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601421" filename="../figg16/G1601421.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 21. Removing Low or High Pressure Switch</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. WRENCHES</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. LOW PRESSURE SWITCH</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring, lubricate the threads with
                    <emph type="bold">mineral-based</emph>
                    refrigerant oil and position the switch on the adapter.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using two wrenches, tighten the low and/or high pressure switch to 7 to 15 ft-lbs. (9.5
                    to 20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the low and/or high pressure switch wires to the wiring harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the covers on the Blend-Air unit and the instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
